# Total War: Warhammer III modding repository.
#
# The chadvandy/mct_wh3 convention (LF) is used because:
#   1. The TWW3 engine's VFS is byte-faithful — it doesn't care about EOL
#   2. The TWW3 modding ecosystem (rpfm, tw_autogen, all known live mods)
#      uses LF
#   3. CA's own data/scripts in the data.pack are stored as LF (the engine
#      normalizes on pack)
#   4. CRLF on Linux/Mac makes diffs ugly; LF is portable
# Windows users get CRLF automatically via the engine's pack normalization.
#
# The rules below match chadvandy/mct_wh3's .gitattributes.

# Auto-detect text files and normalize to LF on commit/checkin.
* text=auto

# Pack files are binary (PFH5 format) — never normalize.
*.pack binary

# Thumbnails are binary.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.ico binary

# Localization TSVs are read as plain text by the engine.
*.tsv text eol=lf
